headline: MAR Q2 Deep Dive: International Strength and Brand Expansion Shape Outlook
summary: Global hospitality company Marriott (NASDAQ:MAR) reported revenue ahead of Wall Street’s expectations in Q2 CY2025, with sales up 4.7% year on year to $6.74 billion. Its non-GAAP profit of $2.65 per share was 1% above analysts’ consensus estimates.
